    • Method Detail

      • getStatisticsEnabled

        @DefaultValue(value="true")
boolean getStatisticsEnabled()

      • getThreadPoolName

        @Optional
String getThreadPoolName()
        Used to search for a org.eclipse.jetty.util.thread.ThreadPool service registered in the kernel by the specified name. If not found then this setting will be ignored.

      • getMaxIdleTime

        @Optional
Integer getMaxIdleTime()
        Set the maximum Idle time for a connection, which roughly translates to the Socket.setSoTimeout(int) call, although with NIO implementations other mechanisms may be used to implement the timeout. The max idle time is applied:
      • When waiting for a new request to be received on a connection
      • When reading the headers and content of a request
      • When writing the headers and content of a response

  • getLowResourceMaxIdleTime

    @Optional
Integer getLowResourceMaxIdleTime()
    The period in ms that a connection is allowed to be idle when there are more than low resource connections. This allows the server to rapidly close idle connections in order to gracefully handle high load situations.

  • getLowResourcesConnections

    @Optional
Integer getLowResourcesConnections()
    The number of connections, which if exceeded places this manager in low resources state. This is not an exact measure as the connection count is averaged over the select sets.

  • getAcceptors

    @Optional
Integer getAcceptors()
    The number of acceptor threads to set.

  • getAcceptorPriorityOffset

    @Optional
Integer getAcceptorPriorityOffset()
    The priority offset of the acceptor threads. The priority is adjusted by this amount (default 0) to either favour the acceptance of new threads and newly active connections or to favour the handling of already dispatched connections.

  • getAcceptQueueSize

    @Optional
Integer getAcceptQueueSize()
    The acceptQueueSize to set.

  • getMaxBuffers

    @Optional
Integer getMaxBuffers()
    The maxBuffers to set.

  • getCorePoolSize

    @Optional
Integer getCorePoolSize()
    How many threads will be created before implementation (execution policy) starts looking for existing free thread. Note that this setting is ignored if getThreadPoolName() resolves to a configured thread pool extension. Additionally, getMaxPoolSize() must be defined as well.

  • getMaxPoolSize

    @Optional
Integer getMaxPoolSize()
    The maximum pool size is the upper bound on how many pool threads can be active at once. Note that this setting is ignored if getThreadPoolName() resolves to a configured thread pool extension. Additionally, getCorePoolSize()} must be defined as well.

  • getPoolKeepAliveTime

    @DefaultValue(value="5000")
Integer getPoolKeepAliveTime()
    If the pool has more than corePoolSize threads and there are more tasks to execute then implementation (execution policy) will terminate all excess threads (maximumPoolSize – coreThreadSize) which are idle for more than this time value in milliseconds. Note that this setting is ignored if getThreadPoolName() resolves to a configured thread pool extension. This value is used in conjunction with getCorePoolSize() and getMaxPoolSize(), This is a BlockingQueue used for holding tasks awaiting execution. There is direct relation between work queue and pool sizing.
